reative and destructive power of language. Through its elaboration of the rich and lively ironies of the Columbus story, The Accidental Indies looks at the nature of storytelling itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMcGill-Queen's University Press eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141957240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773568174423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773568174/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141957-2  McGill-Queen's University Press eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles